Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value of an Annuity} &=\$5,900\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.04067\right)^{10}}}{0.04067}
\\[10pt]
 &=\$5,900\times\dfrac{0.328772642}{0.04067}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$47,695.07}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value of the annuity is $47,695.07.

Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity five years from now.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{\left(1 + 0.04067\right)^{8}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{1.375638369}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$34,671.23}
\end{aligned}$$

**Hence, the annuity value five years from now is $34,671.23.**

Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity three years from now.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{\left(1 + 0.04067\right)^{12}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{1.613453379}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$29,560.86}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the value of the annuity three years from now is $29,560.86.**

Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity today.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{\left(1 + 0.04067\right)^{18}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$47,695.07}{2.049437278}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$23,272.28}
\end{aligned}$$

**As can be seen in our calculation, the value of the annuity today, if it begins nine years from now, is $23,272.28.**

This problem uses the concept of present value annuity which refers to the current value of future payments to be done based on a given time frame and rate. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\text{Cash flow} \times \dfrac{1-\left(\frac{1}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}\right)}{\text{rate}}
\end{aligned}$$

In order to solve for the present value annuity, we can use this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\dfrac{\text{Future value}}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}
\end{aligned}$$
